com.wedeploy.android

Class Call<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wedeploy.android.Call<T>

  • public class Call<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    The Call class encapsulates requests to WeDeploy. In order to invoke a request, you need to invoke execute(), execute(Callback) or asSingle()

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      <any> asSingle()
      Converts this Call object into a Single RxJava object.
      T execute()
      Executes the request synchronously and waits until the response from WeDeploy.

      Executes the request asynchronously.

          throws WeDeployException

      • asSingle

        public <any> asSingle()
        Converts this Call object into a Single RxJava object. You can Single#subscribe() to this object and listen for either a success or failure event.
